text: Hi Akshat. Liquidity increases in the market due to quantitative easing done by the government. This leads to high inflation which can be harmful to a country in the long term. The next step for the government is to reduce the liquidity and suck the money out of the market which is known as tapering. This is mostly done in phases, so the country's market is not shocked by this.
